parameters.text:
=Process the following job opportunity data and extract the structured output.

**INPUT DATA:**
Title: {{ $json.role }}
Company: {{ $json.company }}
Stipend: {{ $json.stipend }}
Eligibility (Raw): {{ $json.eligibility }}
Link: {{ $json.apply_link }}

**VERIFICATION INSTRUCTION:**
1. **Analyze Eligibility:** Check if the scraping result *explicitly* mentions "2027" or "Pre-final".
2. **Ambiguity Trap:** If the scraped text is generic (e.g., just says "Intern" or "B.Tech" without a year), you **MUST** verify using `serpapi_search`.
3. **Search Query:** `{{ $json.company }} {{ $json.role }} internship batch year requirements`

**OUTPUT INSTRUCTIONS:**
- Return ONLY the JSON object.
- **Formatting Check:** Ensure `whatsapp_message` contains actual newlines (`\n`) and NOT literal string characters (`\\n`).

parameters.jsCode:
// 1. Get the raw output from the AI model
// Adjust 'output' if your node names the field differently (e.g., 'text' or 'content')
const rawContent = $input.first().json.output || "";

// 2. Clean the string: Remove Markdown code blocks (```json ... ```)
// This regex removes the start and end code fences
const cleanJson = rawContent.replace(/^```json\s*/i, "").replace(/\s*```$/, "");

// 3. Parse the string into a real JavaScript Array
let jobsArray = [];
try {
  jobsArray = JSON.parse(cleanJson);
} catch (error) {
  // Fallback: If parsing fails, try to return an empty array or log error
  console.log("JSON Parse Error:", error);
  jobsArray = [];
}

// 4. Return separate items for n8n to process
// This automatically "splits" the array so the next node runs 3 times (once for each job)
return jobsArray.map(job => {
  return {
    json: job
  };
});

// 1. Get the raw text string from the Gemini output
// We try two common paths because Gemini node versions vary
const rawResponse = $input.item.json.content?.parts?.[0]?.text || 
                    $input.item.json.output || 
                    "{}";

// 2. Clean up the text (Remove ```json and ``` if the AI added them)
const cleanJson = rawResponse.replace(/```json/g, '').replace(/```/g, '').trim();

// 3. Parse the string into a real JSON object
let parsedData = {};
try {
  parsedData = JSON.parse(cleanJson);
} catch (error) {
  // If parsing fails, return empty fields to prevent workflow crash
  parsedData = {}; 
}

// 4. Return the data as mappable fields
return {
  json: {
    title: parsedData.title || "Unknown Title",
    company_name: parsedData.company_name || parsedData.company || "Unknown Company",
    eligibility: parsedData.eligibility || parsedData.eligibilty || "Check Link",
    link: parsedData.link || ""
  }
};

